<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Heinrich von Seckendorff</head><p>Der Rat teilt mit, dass er nur nach Straßenräubern streifen lässt, aber nicht nach Heinrich oder seinen Freunden.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_311" id="155r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_311_r3l2"><expan>Heinr<ex>ich</ex></expan> <expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan> <expan>Secke<ex>n</ex>dorf</expan> </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_311_r3l3"><expan>Lieb<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>Heınr<ex>ich</ex></expan> / Als Jr vns <expan>v<ex>er</ex>ſchrıb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> habt / vvie ew lantmanſweıſe </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l4">geſagt ſey <expan>word<ex>e</ex>n</expan> / daʒ <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>dıen<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>geſell<ex>e</ex>n</expan> geſtreıfft vnd 
<del rend="strikethrough"><expan>geſcheh<ex>e</ex>n</expan></del></ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l5">
<del rend="strikethrough">ſein / auf ew vnd ewr frewnd vnd geſellen </del> <expan>gehalt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> vnd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l6">das ſüll etwieuil <expan>geſcheh<ex>e</ex>n</expan> ſein / auf ew vnd ewr frewnd vnd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l7"><expan>geſell<ex>e</ex>n</expan> /. Laſſen wir ewr erberkeit wiſſen / daʒ die <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l8"><expan>vnt<ex>er</ex>weılen</expan>
<del rend="strikethrough"> ge </del> ſtreiffen <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>halt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> auf die di auf <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan> ſtraſʒen </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l9">rawben / . Aber wir wiſſen 
<del rend="strikethrough"><expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan> <expan>beſund<ex>er</ex></expan></del> <expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan> <expan>dheine<ex>m</ex></expan> <expan>halt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l10">auf ew 
<del rend="strikethrough"><expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan> die <expan>ewr<ex>e</ex>n</expan></del> / . vnd wiſſen auch nichts das wir </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l11">mit ew cʒeſchıcken <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> <expan>dan<ex>n</ex></expan> lieb vnd güt / . weſten Aber </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l12">die <expan>ewr<ex>e</ex>n</expan> / yemanden <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> / der ſie in <expan>v<ex>er</ex>dehtnüʒʒ</expan> het </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l13">Das lıeſʒt vns mitnamen wiſſen / . So <expan>wolt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l14"><expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>n</expan> red <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> hören / vnd ew <expan>dan<ex>n</ex></expan> <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> ein <expan>antw<ex>ur</ex>t</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_311_r3l15"><expan>wiſſe<ex>n</ex></expan> laſſen / <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> ıj̃ . <expan>p<ex>oſt</ex></expan> Jacobȷ / xȷ<hi rend="sup">o</hi> . </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_311" id="155r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab><expan>Heinr<ex>ich</ex></expan>
<expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>Secke<ex>n</ex>dorf</expan>
</ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Lieb<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>Heinr<ex>ich</ex></expan>, als ir uns
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>schrib<ex>e</ex>n</expan> habt, wie ew
                        lantmansweise gesagt sey <expan>word<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, daz
                                <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>dien<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gesell<ex>e</ex>n</expan> gestreifft und
                            <expan>gehalt<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> und das süll etwievil
                            <expan>gescheh<ex>e</ex>n</expan> sein auf ew und ewr frewnd und
                                <expan>gesell<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, lassen wir ewr erberkeit wissen,
                        daz die <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>unt<ex>er</ex>weilen</expan> streiffen <expan>od<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>halt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> auf die, di auf <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan>
                        straszen rawben. Aber wir wissen <expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>dheine<ex>m</ex></expan>
<expan>halt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> auf ew, und wissen auch nichts, das wir mit
                        ew czeschicken <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, <expan>dan<ex>n</ex></expan>
                        lieb und güt. Westen aber die <expan>ewr<ex>e</ex>n</expan> yemanden
                                <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>, der sie in
                            <expan>v<ex>er</ex>dehtnüzz</expan> het, das lieszt uns mitnamen wissen,
                        so <expan>wolt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir <expan>d<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> red <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> hören und
                        ew <expan>dan<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> ein <expan>antw<ex>ur</ex>t</expan>
<expan>wisse<ex>n</ex></expan> lassen. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> ii <expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan> Jacobi xi<hi rend="sup">o</hi>.</ab>
</div>
